The global thermally conductive plastics market is witnessing significant growth on account of the rising demand for lightweight and efficient materials in various end-use industries. Thermally conductive plastics offer advantages such as superior thermal management, design flexibility, and cost-effectiveness compared to traditional metal alternatives. The increasing need for heat dissipation solutions in electronics, automotive components, and industrial machinery is propelling the market growth. Additionally, the shift towards electric vehicles and the growing trend of miniaturization in electronics are driving the adoption of thermally conductive plastics.

